        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-11-17T13:09:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "When I was looking at an earlier CL, I wondered why you called setImmutable. I guess you did because it matches existing behavior (at least), but it seems strange to me that a side effect of encoding a bitmap is marking it immutable.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 16,
        "startChar": 7,
        "endLine": 16,
        "endChar": 19
      },
      "revId": "537eecf4245deaec2b69a829322fd5935485f394",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "503c1cf2_9d7652f6",
        "filename": "src/images/SkImageEncoder.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 16,
      "author": {
        "id": 5110
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-11-17T17:25:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The temporary bitmap that is on the stack (along with its newly allocated pixref) is marked immutable, just to assert that it never modifies the pixels pointed to by the given pixmap.\n\nThis does not change the mutability of any other bitmap that exists.\n\nIn the future, the SkImageEncoders will work with a hypothetical SkConstPixmap instead of SkBitmaps.",
      "parentUuid": "503c1cf2_5a6e90a9",
      "revId": "537eecf4245deaec2b69a829322fd5935485f394",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
